sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pTet,RBS, GFP, Terminator and pBAD are parts from the registry. The riboswitch is from the Gallivan Lab's paper Synthetic riboswitches that induce gene expression in diverse bacterial species. by Topp et al. in Appl Environ Microbiol. The TAL repressor and TBS are from the Segal Lab at the UC Davis Genome Center. See their paper Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects. by Meckler et al. submitted to Nucleic Acids Res.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Negative control for TAL repressor specificity. TAL repressor 1 expression under the control of a pBAD promoter and a theophylline riboswitch inducible by arabinose and theophylline. The TAL repressor should not be able to bind to the TBS2, since it is not its specific binding site, TBS1 (BBa_K1212004), thus GFP should be expressed if pTet is induced by aTc.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There cannot be a scar between the end of the riboswitch and the start codon of the TAL repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pBAD is a part from the registry. The riboswitch is from the Gallivan Lab's paper Synthetic riboswitches that induce gene expression in diverse bacterial species. by Topp et al. in Appl Environ Microbiol. The TAL repressor is from the Segal Lab at the UC Davis Genome Center. See their paper Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects. by Meckler et al. submitted to Nucleic Acids Res.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: TAL repressor 1 expression under the control of a pBAD promoter and a theophylline riboswitch inducible by arabinose and theophylline.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There cannot be a scar between the end of the riboswitch and the start codon of the TAL repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The pTet promoter, RBS and GFP are all parts from the registry. The TALe binding site is from the Segal Lab at the UC Davis Genome Center. See their paper Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects. by Meckler et al. submitted to Nucleic Acids Res.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pTet promoter upstream of TALe binding site 2 (corresponding to TAL 8 (BBa_K1212007), with B0034 and Golden Gate compatible GFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Appl. Environ. Microbiol. December 2010 vol. 76 no. 23 7881-7884. Synthetic riboswitch generated through rational design and in vivo screening.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Encodes a RNA secondary structure that in the presence of theophylline undergoes a conformational change that makes available the previously sequestered RBS, thus allowing transcription of the downstream sequence. Achieves a 60-fold activation ratio in 2mM theophylline as reported by Topp et al. in: 'Synthetic Riboswitches That Induce Gene Expression in Diverse Bacterial Species.' Appl. Environ. Microbiol. December 2010 vol. 76 no. 23 7881-7884
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: TALe Binding Site 2 (specific to TAL repressor 2)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Synthetic. Assembled in the Segal Lab at UC Davis GBSF. See: 'Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects' by Meckler et al., submitted to Nucleic Acids Research for review.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DNA binding sequence for transcriptional activator like (TAL) repressor 2 (part BBa_K1212006). High binding affinity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Assembled in the Segal Lab at the UC Davis Genome Center. See Quantitative Analysis of TALE-DNA Interactions Suggests Polarity Effects by Meckler et al. submitted to Nucleic Acids Research.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription activator-like (TAL) repressor DNA binding protein that binds to a specific DNA sequence, called TALe Binding Site 1 (TBS 1) (part BBa_K1212003). Low binding affinity.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: K145015 with LVA tag fixed for Golden Gate compatibility through site directed mutagenesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
